TV Independent covered the maiden edition of the US Fair 2019, a trade and investment expo exclusively for Nigerian and American businesses in energy, agriculture, aviation, ICT and others, organized by the U.S. Foreign Commercial Service. U.S. Ambassador W. Stuart Symington delivered remarks at the event, with feature presentations by Mr. Okechukwu Enelamah, Minister of Trade and Investment; Mr. Bismarck Rewane, Managing Director/ CEO, Financial Derivatives and Ms. Yewande Sadiku, CEO, Nigerian Investment Promotion Council. Special Guest of the Occasion, Mr. Worku Gachou, the Managing Director, Africa at the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC), the U.S. Government’s Development Finance Institution. He discussed the establishment of the United States International Development Finance Corporation and a planned $200 million on-lending facility with a Nigerian Financial Institution. —
